raditionally overlooked role of particle-bed impacts in triggering entrainment\nevents in fluvial transport; and the common physical underpinning of transport\nthresholds across aeolian and fluvial environments. This sheds a new light on\nthe well-known Shields diagram, where measurements of fluid entrainment\nthresholds could actually correspond to entrainment-independent cessation\nthresholds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Feb 2020 14:53:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 5 Mar 2020 14:03:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-06"}
